Title: acute visit: UTI
Author: Cover NP, Brianna

1. Urinary tract infection N39.0
UA performed in office and results listed in HPI. Urine will be sent for culture and patient will be called with culture results if they indicate that antibiotic may need to be ineffective. Bactrim DS ordered for patient to take twice daily x5 days. I also ordered Pyridium for patient's complaint of dysuria. Patient encouraged to push fluids, specifically water, and to take antibiotic as directed until completed. Patient advised that if she starts running fever, lower back pain worsens or seems to be one-sided versus another, or if she starts vomiting uncontrollably, then she needs to be seen. Advised patient on side effect profile of antibiotic as well as Pyridium. Patient verbalized understanding about all and has no further questions today.
